          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The Styrene-butadiene dispersion is based on styrene and 1,3-butadiene plus co-monomers like i.e. ac-rylonitrile or (meth-)acrylic acid (ecoinvent v2.2 report 11_III). Following specifications in US Patent 3,875,101 (1971), the dispersion was considered as: 52.5% 1.3-butadiene (0.8571 kg C/kg dry mass); 43% styrene (0.9231 kg C/kg dry mass); 2% acrylic acid (0.5 kg C/kg dry mass); 2.5% acrolein (C3H4O, MW=56; 0.6429 kg C/kg dry mass)</comment>
